# agent-device (physical iPhone)

Use **agent-device** only for app/device automation on a physical iPhone (or simulator). Read [docs/AGENT_DEVICE_SETUP.md](mdc:docs/AGENT_DEVICE_SETUP.md) before first run.

## Bootstrap (every session)

```bash
export DEVELOPER_DIR=/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer
agent-device --version
agent-device help workflow
agent-device devices --platform ios
```

If `agent-device` is missing in the agent terminal but installed globally elsewhere, resolve the absolute binary path from a normal shell; do not assume the agent `PATH` matches the user shell.

## Operating loop

`open -> snapshot -i -> act -> re-snapshot -> verify -> close`

- Exploration: current refs (`@e3`) from `snapshot -i`.
- Durable replay: selectors (`label="…"`, `id="…"`).
- One `--session`: keep mutating commands serial.
- MCP (`agent-device mcp`) is **discovery-only** — automation runs in the integrated terminal, not via MCP tools.

